{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Legally require employers to publish staff disability numbers",
        "additional_details": "I believe sharing this information could motivate companies to strengthen their diversity and inclusion initiatives, especially considering unemployment among visually impaired individuals. Although companies are encouraged to share this data, there is no obligation, so many may choose not to.",
        "background": "The government should require all companies and organisations with employees to disclose the number of disabled individuals they employ, categorised by disability and job type.",
